quran[28]{c,v,t}:
  52,1,By the mount of Tūr
  52,2,and by the Book inscribed
  52,3,on an unrolled parchment
  52,4,"and by the much-frequented House [in heaven]"
  52,5,and by the canopy raised high
  52,6,and by the sea ever filled
  52,7,The punishment of your Lord will surely come to pass
  52,8,there is none who can avert it
  52,9,On the Day when the heaven will convulse violently
  52,10,and the mountains will move a horrible movement
  52,11,then woe to the deniers on that Day
  52,12,those who amuse themselves in falsehood
  52,13,On the Day when they will be shoved into the Fire forcefully
  52,14,"[They will be told,] “This is the Fire which you used to deny"
  52,15,"Is this [punishment] magic, or do you not see"
  52,16,"Burn in it, whether you bear it patiently or impatiently, it makes no difference to you; you are recompensed only for what you used to do.”"
  52,17,"Indeed, the righteous will be in gardens and bliss"
  52,18,"enjoying what their Lord has given them, and their Lord protected them from the punishment of the Blazing Fire"
  52,19,“Eat and drink pleasantly for what you used to do
  52,20,reclining on lined up couches”. And We will marry them to houris of wide beautiful eyes
  52,21,"As for those who believe and their offspring follow them in faith, We will cause their offspring to join them, and will not detract anything from [the reward of] their deeds. Everyone will be accountable for what he earned"
  52,22,And We will provide them with whatever fruit and meat they desire
  52,23,"They will pass around to one another a glass [of pure wine] which does not lead to idle talk or sin"
  52,24,"They will be served by their servant boys, as if they were well-protected pearls"
  52,25,They will turn to one another with questions
  52,26,"They will say, “Before this, we used to be in awe [of Allah] when we were living among our people"
  52,27,Therefore Allah conferred favor upon us and protected us from the punishment of the Scorching Fire
  52,28,"Indeed, we used to call upon Him before. He is indeed the Most Kind, the Most Merciful.”"